text.tspan: State 2, A+B, will hold as long as white is high and grey low
State 3, B, will hold as long as grey is on
State 4, B, will hold as long as white is high
White off Grey off - Hot Water
White on Grey On - heating only
White off Grey On - hold in last position, bad state
If white and grey are both on (heating but no water) and
white goes off, grey will hold motor at B for no good reason
So, if white and grey on, and we want to turn white off,
turn grey off first, then turn white off
